quran[19]{c,v,t}:
  21,94,"So whoever does righteous deeds while he is a believer -his effort will not be ignored, and We shall record it in his favor"
  21,95,No community that We have destroyed can possibly return
  21,96,until Gog and Magog are let loose and they rush down from the heights
  21,97,"Then, the true promise will approach and the eyes of the unbelievers will stare [in horror, while they say], \"Woe to us; we were oblivious to this; rather, we were unjust"
  21,98,You and what you worship other than God are the firewood of Hell. You will be coming to it
  21,99,"Had these [false deities] been [actual] gods, they would not have come to it, but each one of them will stay there [in Hell] forever"
  21,100,In it they will be wailing and they will not be able to hear
  21,101,"As for those for whom We have decreed the best [reward]-they will be kept far removed from Hell"
  21,102,"They will not hear its sound, while they abide eternally in whatever their souls desire"
  21,103,"They will not be grieved by the greatest horror and the angels will greet them, [saying], \"This is your Day which you have been promised"
  21,104,"the Day when We will roll up the heavens as one rolls up a written scroll. Just as We produced the first creation, [so] We will repeat it. This is a binding promise on Us. We will do it"
  21,105,"We have written in the Zabour [Psalms] as We did in previous Scriptures, that My righteous worshipers shall inherit the earth"
  21,106,Truly there is a message in this for people who worship
  21,107,"We have only sent you [Prophet] as a mercy to humanity"
  21,108,"Say, \"It is revealed to me that your god is but one God-so, will you be submissive to Him"
  21,109,"But, if they turn away, then say, \"I have proclaimed the message equally to [all of] you. And I do not know if what you have been promised is near or far"
  21,110,"He knows what is revealed when you speak, and He knows what you conceal"
  21,111,"For all I know [this delay in God's judgment] may be a trial for you and you will have enjoyment for a while"
  21,112,"Say [Prophet] \"My Lord, judge [between us] in Truth. Our Lord is the Merciful-to-all, the one whose help is ever sought against that which you unbelievers speak"